Commentary.Commentary: So with just 106 on the board. It will take some miraculous effort from Bangladesh to get back in this Test. The Indian players will be more than happy with their efforts and are comfortably in the driver's seat. Join us in a while as the Indian openers walk out to bat with the lights starting to take over at this jam-packed Eden Gardens.

Nothing much to talk about Bangladesh's batting. They have once again surrendered without much fight. Only Shadman and Liton showed some grit. Luck too did not go their way as just when Das was looking good, his participation in the game was unfortunately cut short due to concussion. They will be more disappointed as they failed to make even India bowl under proper lights.

Another brilliant performance from India. The spinners bowled a combined total of just 1 over because the pacers were brilliant with the ball. The trio were excellent with the ball. Ishant led the way with 5 while Umesh and Shami had 3 and 2 wickets each. All-in-all the Indian pacers were just too good for the visitors. Special mention for Wriddhiman Saha as he was brilliant behind the stumps and saved a lot of runs.
A 5-wicket haul for Ishant. He leads his side off the field, carving his name in the history books by becoming the first Indian bowler to get a 5-wicket haul in a Day-Night Test.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pujara saves Rohit from another embarrasment of dropping a catch. Sharma had dropped a sitter in the first Test match and he was on the verge of dropping another but it was not to be as Pujara saved him. Good length ball outside off, Jayed looks to guide it to third man but the ball goes off his outside edge towards Rohit Sharma at second slip. He makes a mess of it and has no idea where the ball has gone. Luckily for him, the ball lands straight into the hands of Pujara at first slip. With this, Bangladesh have been BOWLED OUT FOR JUST 106.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Jayed looks to flick it but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads. No run.
Short ball on middle, Al-Amin looks to pull it but the ball goes off the top edge towards cover. The batters cross over for a single.
Length ball on off, Abu does well to get bat on ball.
The last man in is Abu Jayed.

OUT! Bowled! 5-fer for Ishant Sharma. His 10th in Tests. A proper outswinger this. Ishant uses the width of the crease and bowls it on middle. It shapes away from the batter. Nayeem looks to defend it away from his body. He misses and the off stump goes for a toss. Second 5-fer at home for Ishant. 12 years after his first.
Fuller ball on off, Nayeem looks to play it on the off side but it goes off the outer half of his bat through covers. Umesh cleans it up. Two taken.
Bouncer! It is very close to the body. Nayeem takes his eyes off the ball and keeps his bat hanging with his bottom hand off the bat. It hits him on the handle of his bat.
Full on middle and off, Nayeem defends it to the on side.
Pacy inswinger pitching on middle and leg. Nayeem looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length ball outside off, Hossain looks to play the drive but is beaten.  Another good over from Shami comes to an end.
BOUNCER! A good one at that! It is bowled on middle, Hossain ducks under it.
The batsman has played it to the point region.

FALLS SHORT! Short ball outside off, Nayeem looks to play the upper cut but it goes off the upper half of his bat towards third man. Jadeja runs in to take the catch but the ball falls short. It hits his hand and the ball goes towards the fence. Jadeja recovers and cleans it up. The batters take a single. If Jadeja can't catch that one, then I doubt that anyone can.

FOUR LEG BYES! Full delivery down the leg side, Hasan looks to flick it but it brushes his thigh pad and goes to the fine leg fence. The replays roll in and it shows that it should have been given as byes as there was nothing on it. 100 up for the visitors.
BEATEN! Good length ball with some late swing outside off, Nayeem looks to guide this to third man but fails to put any bat on it.
Al-Amin Hossain walks out at number 10. Technically the 11th batsman as both Liton and Mehidy batted.

OUT! CAUGHT! The concussion substitute has to go. Full delivery on middle, Mehidy flicks this uppishly but he finds Pujara at short mid-wicket. He dives forward and takes the catch just inches above the ground. The square leg umpire has told Mehidy Hasan to wait in order to check whether it was a clean catch which it is and Mehidy has to go. Bangladesh have not even reached 100 and they are just two wickets away from getting bowled out.
PLAY AND A MISS! Ishant dishes out a full delivery outside off, Mehidy attempts the drive but misses it altogether yet again.
Full delivery on off, Mehidy pushes it to cover for nothing.
BEATEN! A wild slash this one though. Shorter delivery outside off, Mehidy attempts the cut shot but fails to make any connection to it.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Mehidy defends it to mid on.
Good length ball on off, MH defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Good length ball on off, Nayeem defends it to cover off the back foot.
Short ball outside off, Nayeem attempts to play the upper cut but misses it altogether.
FOUR! Nicely played! Back of a length delivery outside off, Nayeem camps on his back foot and punches it to deep point for a boundary.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shami bowls a length ball on off, Nayeem on his back foot guides it over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Full delivery on middle, Nayeem plays it back to Shami.
Good length ball on off, Nayeem pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish ball on off, Mehidy is solid in defense. A better over for Bangladesh as 8 runs have come off it.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This man is showing that he can bat. Full delivery outside off, Mehidy lunges forward and thrashes the ball through covers and into the fence.
Back of a length ball outside off, Mehidy shoulders arms to it.
Short ball on off, Mehidy rocks on his back foot and defends it onto the pitch.
Good length ball on off, Mehidy defends it towards cover.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Fullish delivery around off, Mehidy prods forward and guides this towards the backward point region for his first boundary.
OHH! Another short ball on leg stump! Nayeem tries to fend at it but it hits him on the body.
On a length outside off, Nayeem guides it to point for nothing.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Nayeem looks to guide it to third man but fails to put any bat to it.
BOUNCER! Shami goes for another bumper on middle, Nayeem ducks under it.

BEATEN! Beautiful bowling but an even better take from Saha! Good length ball on off moving in. Nayeem looks to defend it but the ball smeaks through. Saha dives full length to his right and pouches it safely. Excellent stuff from Wriddhiman.
Full delivery down the leg side, Nayeem looks to flick it but misses it completely.
Full delivery on off, Mehidy defends it to point.

The concussion based substitute has been made. Mehidy Hasan is the one who is brought on in place of Liton Das and he is out to bat now. Remember he is a like for like substitute so he can just bat and not bowl in this game.

OUT! TIMBER! After bowling some balls outside off, Ishant goes full and hits the stumps. Briliant bowling this! Full delivery on off, Hossain looks to defend while he moves to the leg side but fails to make any connection to it. The ball whizzes past the bat and goes onto hitting the stumps. The visitors crumbel further.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Ebadot looks to drive but misses it altogether.

Fullish delivery outside off, Ebadot guides it to point where Jadeja misfields allowing the batsmen to take a single. They crossed over for a couple but umpire Erasmus has found Hossain one short. So only a single given.
BEATEN! Another full delivery outside off, Ebadot looks to drive yet again but fails to make any connection to it.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Hossain attempts the drive but the ball passes the outside edge of his bat and Saha collects it behind the stumps.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Shami goes full outside off, Nayeem creams the drive through cover for the second boundary of the over.
OUCH! This time hits the gloves. Shami bowls another short delivery opn middle, Nayeem looks to fend it off the back foot but the ball hits the gloves and goes onto the pitch.

EXCELLENT TAKE FROM SAHA AGAIN! This is a beautiful piece of bowling from Shami! Good length ball on off swinging in. Nayeem looks to defend it but the ball cuts him in half. The ball flies to the right of Saha who does very well to catch it while diving.
FOUR! Nicely played that! Short ball outside off, Hasan rocks on his back foot and plays the upper cut over the second slip fielder to get off the mark with a boundary.
Another short ball but this time down the leg side, Nayeem looks to pull at the last moment but ball goes past him and into the mitts of the keeper.

Another vicious Shami bouncer that hits the helmet. This time it is the helmet of Nayeem. The physio will have another run out. To have a concussion test on Nayeem. Nayeem is smiling so this should not be as bad as Liton's, at least we all hope so. Nayeem looks fine to continue at this point of time.

OUCH! Another bumper which goes on to hit the helmet. Shami bowls a bouncer on middle. Nayeem looks to sway away from it but cannot do so. It goes onto hit the helmet and up in the air. Kohli from the slips goes behind and takes the catch with a single hand. The Indians check up on Hasan and he is seen sharing a smile with his partner suggesting that he is fine. Physio called in to check up on him. Let's see whether he will continue or not.
Mohammad Shami to bowl the first full over of the session.
BEATEN! Beautiful ball from Ishant! Good lenght ball outside off, Hossain looks to defend it but the ball whizzes past the bat and into the keeper's gloves.
Bowls a full delivery outside off, Ebadot does not fiddle with it and leaves it well alone.

We are back for the second session! Nayeem Hasan is coming out to bat? Who will it be along with him? Will it be Liton Das or someone else? It is Ebadot Hossain who joins Nayeem out in the middle. The Indian players are also making their way out to the middle. Ishant Sharma will finish his over.
... Day 1, Session 2 ...

Just like the first Test, Bangladesh struggled after opting to bat. Three ducks amongst the top 5 batsmen makes it obvious that they have had a nightmare. Only Shadman and Liton looked good. The former departed after a good start. The real cause of concern for Bangladesh is Liton who has also departed due to concussion. They will hope that he is fine to bat after the break as they do not have many options on the bench. What will happen? Join us after the break to find out.

Pink ball or red ball, it does not matter to this Indian fast bowling unit. Another Test and another session dominated by the Indian pacers. They were off colour at the start but have gotten better as they got the better grip of this pink ball. Umesh, Ishant and Shami all got into the wickets column, with 3, 2 and 1 respectively. Just a solitary over of spin in this session. Also a special shout-out for Wriddhiman Saha who has had to face the real challenge with the pink ball but he has been magnificent behind the stumps. Not just picking up a stunner but also saving runs.

Oh no! Not good news this. Liton Das is showing symptoms of concussion here and the umpire has called for the physio. He seems to be a bit dizzy. Though Liton has looked very good he should not continue as nothing is more important than health and a blow to the head can be very dangerous. Liton is walking off and so are the players. That will be Lunch on Day 1.
Ishant bowls a length delivery outside off, Das lets the ball pass through to the keeper.
Another full delivery outside off, Das lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside off, Das does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to Saha.

FOUR! Beautiful shot from Liton Das! He is looking in terrific touch out there. Ishant bowls a half-volley outside off, Das lunges forward and creams the drive to deep extra cover for another boundary.
On a length on middle, Das looks to defend it but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards square leg. The batters cross for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Das lets the ball go to the keeper.
FOUR! This is how you reply after being hit on the grill. Short ball on off, Liton rocks on his back foot and pulls it with full authority to square leg for a boundary.
The physio is out to have a mandatory concussion test on Liton Das.

OUCH! That surely has hurt Das! Short ball on middle, Das looks to play the hook shot but the ball goes and hits his helmet. The ball rolls to point. Mohammed Shami and the rest enquire whether he is fine to continue. The physio is being called for the mandatory concussion check.
Good length ball on off, Das defends it to point.
Shami is back. 5-1-13-1, his figures so far.

FOUR BYES! Beautiful bowling from Ishant Sharma! Good length ball swinging into the batsman. Nayeem looks to fend it but the ball cuts him in half, and goes right between the bat and pad. Saha dives to his left to collect it but fails to do so. The ball rolls to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Nayeem looks to flick it away but it goes off his thigh pad towards square leg.
The new man in is Nayeem Hasan.

OUT! CAUGHT! First it was Rohit Sharma who took a blinder, now it is Saha who takes what we can call a superhero catch. Brilliant stuff from the Indian keeper. Ishant Sharma bowls it on a length around off, the ball swings a bit late. Mahmudullah looks to defend it but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. Saha, the local lad, dives to his right and takes a stunning catch inches above the ground with just one hand. Bangladesh lose their sixth wicket and slip further and further.
Full delivery around off, Mahmudullah pushes it to cover-point for nothing.
Good length ball on off, Mahmudullah blocks it back to Ishant.
Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah shoulders arms and lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish delivery on middle, Das works it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery outside off, Das plays it to cover off the back foot.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Low full toss on middle and leg, Liton flicks it to deep mid-wicket and picks up his third boundary of the innings.
Tossed up ball on middle and leg, Mahmudullah flicks it to the leg side and takes a single.
Floated ball outside off, Mahmudullah pushes it to covers and wants a single but Das is not interested.
Jadeja starts with a flighted ball on middle, Mahmudullah plays it back to the bowler.
Spin time. Ravindra Jadeja is into the attack now.
Full delivery in the channel outside off, Liton once more does not fiddle with it.
This time bowls it on a length outside off, Das has no problems in leaving this one alone.
Fullish ball outside the off stump, Das shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on off, Liton drives this beautifully but finds the fielder at cover who dives to his right to stop the ball.
Full delivery outside off, Das lunges forward and pushes it to point for a couple. Shubman Gill runs after it and cleans it up.
Starts with a full delivery on middle, Das pushes it back to Ishant.
Ishant Sharma is back on. Figures are 5-2-5-1 so far.
BOUNCER! Umesh bowls this on off, Mahmudullah who does well to duck under it.
Fullish delivery outside off, Mahmudullah blocks it to cover and looks for a single but is sent back by Das. Good decision as the single was not there.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Poor ball from Yadav! He tends to stray down sometimes. Bowls it on the pads, Mahmudullah flicks it to fine leg and picks up an easy boundary.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Umesh Yadav! Good length ball outside off swinging away, Mahmudullah looks to defend it but passes the outside edge of the bat to the keeper.

Good length ball around off, it comes back in. Mahmudullah looks to defend but it goes off his thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is not interested. The umpire waits and then signals it as run. Hawk Eye later on rolls in and it shows that the bat was not involved. It also shows that it was going over the stumps.
Outside off, Mahmudullah leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Das nudges it to point for one.
Full and coming in. Das gets on his front foot and does well to defend it.
On off, Das defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on the pads, Das works it to the leg side.
Single to end the over. On the pads, LD looks to glance it to the leg side but it goes off his pad and they take a leg bye.
FOUR! Poor ball and rightfully punished. Liton looks to be in the mood here. Length ball well outside off, Das slams it through backward point for a boundary.
Now calmly leaves the length ball outside off.
FOUR! Liton is off the mark in style. Slightly overpitched on the pads, Liton picks it early and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Liton Das walks out to the middle now. He looked good in the last Test but failed to convert his start. Can he do something special here?

OUT! Caught! Beautiful delivery from Umesh. Hardly anything Shadman could do. Bangladesh have half their side back in the hut now. Good length ball around off, Shadman is in two minds whether to play at it or not. He decides to have a poke at it. The ball shapes away and tickles the outside edge. It goes straight to Saha. He will not drop those even in his sleep. Half the side back in the pavilion. 100th Test dismissal for Wriddhiman Saha. Join quickest for India to achieve this feat for India along with Dhoni. One of the easiest ones to get to this landmark.
Full and wide outside off, Shadman looks to drive but misses.
Shami wants Mahmudullah to drive but Mahmudullah is not tempted to and leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah leaves it alone.

FOUR BYES! This one does too much. Good length ball down the leg side, the ball keeps going away to the left of Saha. He dives but has no chance of saving that and the ball goes to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball on middle and off, Shadman looks to defend but it goes to the leg side off the inner half of his bat for a single.
Length ball way outside off. Shadman looks to cut but it comes off the lower half of his bat. It goes to the left of point. Jadeja there moves there swiftly and keeps it to a dot.
On the fourth stump line, Shadman leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Mahmudullah lets the ball go to the keeper.

EDGED BUT FALLS WELL SHORT! Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah attempts to defend it but it goes off the outside edge towards Saha who collects it on the bounce diving forward. Played it with soft hands and that's probably why it did not carry to Wriddhiman Saha.
Short delivery on off, Shadmap pulls it towards deep square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! Strays down the leg side does Umesh Yadav! It is bowled on a length, which is picked off easily by Shadman Islam and goes into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
On a length outside off, Shadman guides it to covers and takes a couple before the fielder from third man can clean it up.
Full delivery on off, Shadman plays it back to the bowler.
Shami fires another pacy ball. It is down the leg side though. Mahmudullah looks to flick but misses. End of a brilliant Shami over.
Mahmudullah is the new man in.

OUT! Chopped on! Bangladesh's crisis man is out of here and the misery piles on. Back of a length ball on off, Mushfiqur looks to defend but he is a bit late on it. The ball takes the upper half of his bat and goes onto hit the stumps. A similar way in which Mushfiqur got out in the first Test. India did not look too good with the ball to start off with but now they are looking at their lethal best!
On the pads, Islam glances it to the on side for a single.
FOUR! This time looked a bit more controlled. Good length ball around off, Shadman looks to run it down to third man but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of gully for a boundary.
EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball on off, Shadman looks to drive but the ball moves away taking the outside edge of the bat and it goes over the man at third slip for a boundary.
Bouncer. It is outside the stumps, Islam looks to pull but then leaves it.
On the fourth stump line, Rahim does not disturb that one. End of a magnificent over from Umesh.
On the pads, Mushfiqur flicks it to the on side.
Length ball on off, Rahim plays it to point to start his innings.
Mushfiqur Rahim walks out to the middle. Bangladesh under the pump here and need Mushfiqur to bail them out.

OUT! BOWLED! Umesh strikes again. Wicket, dot, wicket. This has been a brilliant over. Umesh fires one full ball which comes back in. Mithun looks to defend but gets a slight inside edge which takes the leg stump out for a toss. The crowd is up in joy and Bangladesh in deep, deep trouble here.
Fuller on off, Mithun starts his innings with a front foot defense.
Mohammad Mithun is the new man in.

OUT! Caught! Rohit Sharma has taken a stunner here! Good length ball around off, it shapes away at the last moment. It is in the channel of uncertainty. Mominul looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. It goes between first and second slip. Rohit Sharma at second slip dives to his right and takes a superb one-handed catch. Had he not dived, one would feel it would have gone straight to Kohli but as they say if you feel like it is your catch at slip then you should go for it. That is exactly what Rohit has done here. The Bangladesh skipper departs for a duck.
Outside off, Islam leaves it alone.

WOW! This one has moved a long long way. Excellent take from Saha. Saha has found the toughest so far with this pink ball. Shami goes wide of the crease and makes it jag back in. The ball keeps coming in and it keeps going away from the wicketkeeper. as it goes to Saha. He dives to his right and saves a certain FOUR BYES.
Back of a length around off, Islam defends it off his back foot.

Length ball on off, Shadman defends it towards point. Mominul was looking to steal a single but Shadman says no. Umesh Yadav has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Even if Umesh had hit Mominul would have been in. Good call from Shadman as the single was not there at all.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on the fourth stump line. Shadman leaves it alone.
Outside off and swinging away. Shadman shoulders arms to it. Once again there is swing once the ball is past the stumps.
Back of a length on off, Shadman defends it with soft hands to the off side and takes a quick single to keep the strike.
Fuller outside off, Shadman does not play at it.
Jags this one back in. On middle and off, Islam defends it well.
Closer to the off pole but still outside. Shadman shoulders arms to this once again Smith style.
Good keeping this from the local boy. Good length ball outside off, Shadman leaves it alone. The ball moves a lot after the stumps and Saha does really well to take it with a dive to his left.
Length ball outside off, away swing on this one. Shadman has no interest in playing that.
On the body, Mominul tucks it to the on side. Exciting over from Shami first up.
Good length ball on off, Mominul defends it onto the ground. It hits him on his body off the surface and goes to the off side.
Back of a length ball outside off, Mominul leaves it alone.
Short ball around the body, Shadman pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review from India! How come Saha did not pick this one up? Shami bowls a good length ball swinging in. Shadman looks to defend it but the sneaks past the bat and pad going to Wriddhiman Saha who dives to his right to take the catch. The Indians appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Shami and Saha look confident and convince Kohli to go for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is clearly no bat on it. The ball has gone off the thigh pad and into the keeper's gloves. Both teams lose a review very early on in the game. What a start to the spell from the local lad, Mohammed Shami.
Review time again. This time it is India who have taken it for a caught behind. It looks to be missing the bat but let's see what the replays have to say.

Almost gets a wicket off the first ball Shami bowls! Bowls it a shorter outside off, Shadman looks to leave the ball alone. It goes off the bottom half of the bat uppishly. Shami hares towards it to take the catch but it bounces way short. Lucky break for Shadman Islam.
Mohammed Shami is into the attack for the first time.
Back of a length ball on off, Mominul hops and keeps it down. End of a very successful over from Ishant. Wicket maiden.
Outside off, Haque leaves it alone.
Bouncer to welcome the Bangladesh skipper. Mominul sways away from it.
Bangladesh skipper, Mominul Haque comes out at number 3.

OUT! LBW! India have their first wicket with the pink ball. It looked to be hitting the stumps and it is indeed hitting the leg stump. Slightly fuller on around off, Kayes gets across and looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his front pad and the Indian players go up in a confident appeal. The umpire agrees with them and raises his finger. Kayes has a word with his partner and reviews it. Replay rolls in. Ultra Edge first comes in and confirms no involvement of bat. Ball Tracker then comes in and it shows that the ball was going to hit the leg pole. Bangladesh lose their review. Kayes does not survive for long. The fans are up in joy and so are the players.
Review time! This time Imrul Kayes has been given out LBW. It looks plumb to the naked eye. Let's see what the replays have to say.
Outside off, Kayes leaves it alone. This one swings leaps and bounds.

NOT OUT! It has indeed come off his thigh pad. Kayes straightaway reviewed it indicating that the ball had come off his thigh pad and that is indeed the case. Back of a length around off, the ball jags away at the end. Kayes looks to defend but it goes off something behind to the keeper. The Indian players appeal and the umpire raises his finger after a brief thought. Kayes signals the 'T' straightaway. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows no spike as it goes past the bat. The on-field decision is overturned and Kayes survives.
Review time. Imrul Kayes has been given out caught. Kayes has immediately reviewed it indicating it did not hit his bat. Let's see what the replays have to say.
Good length delivery on off, Islam attempts to defend it but it hits the outside half of the bat and rolls towards point.
Islam, yet again, lets this good length ball outside off go to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Islam does not fiddle with it and allows the ball to go to the keeper.
LEG BYE! Umesh Yadav bowls a good length ball on the pads, Kayes looks to flick it but the ball hits the pads and goes towards square leg. The batters steal a leg bye.
On a length on middle, Imrul works it to the leg side.
Good length ball on off, Kayes blocks it to point.
Another one outside off, Ishant wants Shadman to drive but Islam is not interested.
Way outside off, Shadman leaves it in a similar way to Steven Smith.
Outside off, Islam leaves it alone.
Ishant makes this one come back in to the southpaw. Shadman hops on his crease and blocks it to the off side.
This one comes with the angle on off and middle. Kayes glances it using the angle through square leg for one.
On the fourth stump line, Imrul looks to play but then leaves it alone.
Full delivery outside off, Islam shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Thrashed! Umesh Yadav bowls a shorter delivery around off, Islam camps on his back foot and pulls it with disdain over the mid-wicket fielder for the second boundary of the over.
On a length on middle, Islam works it to square leg.
FOUR! Poor ball this from Umesh Yadav! Bowls it on a length way outside off, Shadman Islam stands tall and hammers the ball away through covers for the first boundary of the game.
Full delivery down the leg side, Shadman looks to flick it but the ball glances his pad and goes to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Shadman shoulders arms to this one.
Good amount of swing on this one. Outside off and swinging away. Kayes leaves it alone. Saha moves to his right and gathers the ball.
On the pads, Imrul glances it through square leg and gets a couple as Mayank Agarwal cleans it up with a slide.
This one comes in. Good length ball on off, Kayes looks to defend but does so off the outer half of his bat towards gully.
Length ball on off, Shadman nudges it to cover-point and gets a single.

Beautiful! Ishant shows the seam and hits the deck hard around off, Shadman looks to defend but gets squared up as the ball moves away at the last moment. It was not far away from the edge and the off pole.
Hint of away movement for Ishant. Good length ball outside off, Shadman initially looks to defend but then leaves it alone. Ishant a tad shorter than his usual lengths.
Full on off, Imrul defends it to the on side to get through the over. 2 off Umesh's first but the swing he generated will excite him.
Fuller outside off, Kayes lets it carry to the keeper.
Shadman gets underway as well. On the pads, Islam flicks it to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Umesh is generating the swing here unlike his partner. Full and it comes in to the southpaw. Shadman defends it off the front foot.
Bangladesh up and running. On the pads, Kayes glances it to fine leg and gets off the mark. First run for Bangladesh with the pink ball.
Umesh comes over the wicket and bowls a full ball on off. Imrul starts his innings with a solid front foot defense. Hint of inward swing for Umesh.
Umesh Yadav to partner Ishant Sharma from the other end.
Full outside off, Shadman leaves it alone. There is a bit of away swing on this one but that comes once the ball is past the stumps. Maiden to begin with.
Back of a length ball around the pads, Shadman tucks it to the on side.
Ishant goes full on middle and off, Shadman defends it with a straight bat. Not a lot of movement for Ishant so far.
Length ball closer to the off pole, Shadman defends it to point.
A slight bit of away movement on this one. Good length ball outside off, Ishant makes the ball curve away a bit. Shadman does not disturb that.
Ishant comes around the wicket and bowls it on the pads with the angle. No swing first up just the ball going with the angle. Shadman glances it to square leg.

Done and Dusted with the national anthems. Bangladesh Prime Minister, Sheikh Hasina and Bengal Chief Minister, Mamta Banerjee ring the bell. The Indian players are in a huddle before they take their respective positions in the field. Shadman Islam and Imrul Kayes walk out to the middle to become the first openers to open the innings for Bangladesh in Day/Night Test. Ishant Sharma will have the honors to be the first bowler to bowl with the pink ball for India. Shadman Islam will face the first ball.
Both set of players along with the umpires and the match referee walk out to the middle for their national anthems. We are very close from the historic Test to begin!

Indian coach Ravi Shastri is down for a quick interview with Laxman Sivaramakrishnan. Ravi Shastri says that they have not played this too often so it will be a wait and watch game. Tells the biggest challenge is how the pink ball will behave. Feels that the biggest challenge is that it should have the challenges of proper Test cricket. On the ball, he says that it is a bit heavier and one will have to keep their eyes on the ball till the very end. On how he manages the current team, he says there is a wealth of talent and it is harder now as it is difficult to find a way to get them in the Playing XI. Shastri says that the players in the Playing XI cannot take their place for granted as there is someone ready to take their place.

India (UNCHANGED PLAYING XI) - Mayank Agarwal, Rohit Sharma, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli(C), Ajinkya Rahane, Ravindra Jadeja, Wriddhiman Saha(WK), Umesh Yadav, Ravichandran Ashwin, Mohammed Shami, Ishant Sharma.

Bangladesh (PLAYING XI) - Shadman Islam, Imrul Kayes, Mominul Haque(C), Mohammad Mithun, Mushfiqur Rahim, Mahmudullah, Liton Das(WK), Nayeem Hasan (IN PLACE OF MEHIDY HASAN), Abu Jayed, Al-Amin Hossain (IN PLACE OF TAIJUL ISLAM), Ebadot Hossain.

Indian skipper, Virat Kohli says that even he would have batted first as the pitch looks good. Though Kohli thinks that it is not a bad thing though as the new pink ball will do something in the start. Adds that there is something underneath the surface and feels that the ball will do something later on as well. On what are the challenges, Kohli says they have to be very precise and thinks all the bowlers and fielders need to be more alert especially in the first hour. On what it means to be part of this history, he says that it is a responsibility and feels proud as a lot of legends have played before them and it is a proud moment for him and the team.

Mominul Haque, the Bangladesh skipper says they will bat first. Goes on to say that the wicket is on a drier side and that's why they are looking to bat first. Adds that it is a very good decision to bat first. Further says that playing a pink ball Test is a very good feeling and his friends and family are there to watch the game. Says that there are two changes for them.

TOSS - We are all set for the iconic moment as both the captains walk out to the middle for their first ever toss in a Day-Night Test. Indian skipper, Virat Kohli has the special coin in hand. Up it goes and it comes down in favour of Mominul Haque. BANGLADESH OPT TO BAT.

PITCH REPORT - Deep Dasgupta is the pitch analyst for the day and he is down now for the pitch report. Further says that there is a bit of grass and it is a bit dry. Dasgupta says that it might be a bit dry keeping dew in mind. Deep insists that it will be dry especially in the first innings. Reckons the team winning the toss should bat first.

Welcome to the 2nd and final test between India and Bangladesh. A historic Test at an iconic venue. The much talked about pink ball makes its entry in India. Both sides enter pastures new as they make their debut in Day-Night Test. The hosts would look to continue their dominance and inflict another whitewash in Tests. Unsure of how much factor dew will play, it will be interesting to see whether India go for their tried and tested formula of 2 spinners at home or will they remove one of them. Bangladesh, on the other hand, will have to be at their brilliant best it they are to surprise the cricketing world. It will be interesting to see whether or not they make any changes to their side after a horror show at Indore. In a filled Eden Gardens, can the Bangla Tigers roar so loud that it makes everyone else silent or will India continue their dominance?

Bangladesh's bowling was completely flat to say the least and their fielding too wasn't up to the mark. They were always behind the 8-ball and their only moment of joy came after they took the second new ball. Their bowlers made it talk and picked up four wickets in quick time. Al-Amin Hossain, Abu Jayed and Ebadot Hossain picked 8 wickets among themselves but failed to create the kind of impact Bangladesh would have wanted. Now, it's up to their batsmen to show some fight and resilience against the lethal pace battery of India. They have a deficit of 241 to negate first. Do join us in a short while.

Summing up India's reply to Bangladesh's paltry first innings total, once again it was their skipper, Virat Kohli, who stood up to the challenge of the alien conditions and notched up yet another century in his illustrious career. Pujara and Rahane batted around him to construct vital partnerships and together, it was a strong reply by the home team against some lacklustre bowling by the Bangla team.

Here comes the declaration! Virat Kohli feels he has got enough in the kitty and the last pair ain't adding much. Also, he wants his pacers to get the taste of bowling under lights with the pink ball. Tough time ahead for the Bangladeshi batsmen.
Length ball going away, Saha defends it to point.
Bouncer. Another one and Saha gets away from it on its way to the keeper.
Bouncer! Saha ducks under it. Good spirit from Al-Amin, he wants to dish it out.

Down the leg side. Saha looks to flick but misses.
Full on the pads, Saha flicks it. The ball goes to deep square leg but they do not take the single.

Ishant looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal and umpire agrees with him. Ishant has a word with Saha and then takes it to the T.V umpire. Replay rolls in. OUT! Caught! Umesh walks off for a duck. Full around off, Umesh swings his bat wildly at it but gets a thick outside edge which goes straight to second slip. Shadman Islam makes no mistake. No Umesh blast in the pink ball Test at Kolkata.
Length ball outside off, Umesh looks to play at it but misses.

Umesh Yadav is the new man.

The ball hits his pad and there is a huge appeal from the Bangladesh bowlers. Umpire Joel Wilson raises his finger after a few thoughts. Ashwin has a word with Saha and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and it shows the impact is just about umpire's call. India don't lose their review but Ashwin has to walk back.
Review time! Ashwin has been adjudged LBW and he has taken it upstairs after consulting his partner. The impact looks to be an issue but let's see what the replays have to say.
Good length ball on off, it jags back in. Wriddhiman Saha defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on middle, Saha flicks it to the on side for a single.
Bangladesh struggling to control the new pink ball under lights. Fuller down the leg side. Saha looks to flick but misses.
Full on off,  Saha keeps it out.

Al-Amin Hossain is back.

FOUR BYES! Another wild delivery this time down the leg side. Ashwin looks to pull but misses. Mithun dives but has absolutely no chance of saving that. It goes to the fence. Four byes signalled. Ebadot is a lucky man as it has not been wided.
WIDE! Wild delivery outside off. Ashwin leaves it alone as the ball is well over the tramline.

FOUR! Poor fielding from Abu Jayed. Full and jagging back in Ashwin flicks it through square leg. Abu Jayed comes running in and looks to stop it with a dive but he cannot do it cleanly. The ball deflects off his body and into the fence.
FOUR BYES! Short ball down the leg side. Ashwin looks to pull but misses. Mithun dives to his left but fails to stop it and the ball goes to the fence.
Full on the pads, Ashwin flicks it to fine leg and keeps the strike.
Length ball outside off, Ashwin leaves it alone.

Review time! It is for a catch. It looks nothing on the naked eye let's see what the replays have to say.

Full outside off, Ashwin shoulders arms to it. The ball reaches to the keeper around chest height. Good bounce on this one.

Good length ball outside off, Ravichandran leaves it alone.

OUT! Caught! Superman catch by Taijul! He is showing his teammates how to field. In Taijul's previous over there was a lethargic effort and he was not happy and he shows why. Poor ball from Ebadot. It is full on the pads, a nothing delivery. Kohli flicks it uppishly looking to score a maximum. Tajul, who is standing ahead of the ropes at deep backward square leg, runs, stretches and dives to his right to pluck this out of thin air and takes a blinder. Kohli's brilliant innings comes to an end. He walks off with a smile as even he cannot believe what has happened. Something special was needed to get rid of King Kohli and something magical has happened.
Length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone. Extra bounce on this one.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball around off, it comes in a bit off the deck. Kohli looks to play it on the on side but he is a bit late in his shot and the ball goes off the leading edge towards the backward point fence for a boundary.

Second new ball is available and it has been immediately taken by Bangladesh! Ebadot Hossain is brought back into the attack to make the first use of the new nut. Two wickets to his name so far. Can he add more to his tally?
Shorter on middle and leg, Saha watches it till the end and defends this off his back foot.

Another one-sided session of Test cricket thoroughly dominated by India! Virat Kohli has notched up a century yet again and it's business as usual for the home team. Their lead has zoomed to a significant number in India's cricket history (183) and they have closed almost all the doors on Bangladesh. Only saving grace for the visitors was the wicket of Ajinkya Rahane and apart from that they were substandard with their bowling and fielding. Currently going through the motions, Bangladesh need a spark of inspiration from somewhere. Will it come after Lunch? Do join us at 1540 local (1010 GMT) for the second session.

HUNDRED FOR KOHLI! Number 27 in Tests! The captain leading from the front. This has been a brilliant knock from the skipper. He gets into the history books by becoming the first Indian to get a century in a Day-Night Test. Floated around the pads, Virat glances it behind square on the leg side and takes a couple to get to his milestone. Virat removes his helmet and raises his bat as the crowd and his teammates rise and applaud the knock from the King! His 41st century as skipper across all formats, joint most. Equals Ricky Ponting's record. Time to convert this into another double hundred, Super V?

Drinks break! After toiling hard for an hour, Bangladesh managed to pick a wicket against the run of play. From the point of view of this Test match, India are well ahead, by 130 runs to be precise, and the home team continues to march forward. Virat Kohli is nearing his century and that should keep the fans engaged in the next hour. For Bangladesh, they are going through the motion and need to increase their intensity in the field. Pitch report - Sunil Gavaskar starts by saying that Bangladesh's batting was very ordinary on Day 1. Feels they got overwhelmed by the occasion and adds that the full house can deter any team. Tells that the ball didn't swing as much as it did in Indore and it was poor batting. Reckons that it's still a very good pitch to bat on. Mentions that the batsmen need to be careful early on and then there will be runs on offer. Praises the groundsmen for thinking out of the box as they used jute bags and extra protection to avoid dew setting in on the ground during the last session. The Little Master signs off by reiterating that the pitch is full of runs.

13 wickets, a fifer for a bowler, not one but two concussion substitutes, Bangladesh getting overawed by the situation, Indian openers getting dismissed cheaply for a change, Pujara and Kohli showing their mettle under demanding conditions - Those were the highlights of the first day of the historic Day-Night Test at Eden Gardens, Kolkata. It was truly action-packed and this match has moved at a very brisk pace. Already the home team has got a 68-run lead and with plenty of batting left in the tank, they will aim to build Mount Everest in front of their Asian neighbours. A one-way traffic it has been and we are expecting more of the same today. Can Bangladesh surprise and prove us wrong? Hello and welcome everyone for the coverage and stay with us to find out.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 ...

So 13 wickets fell on the first day of this historic pink-ball Test. India have a healthy lead of 68 and they will look to make it an unassailable one on Day 2. Bangladesh will hope that it is a better day on Saturday and they can somehow manage to restrict India to a bare minimum. What's in store for us on Day 2? Join us on Saturday, 23rd November to find out. The play will start at 1300 local (0730 GMT). Till then, have a good time!

A tough day's play for Bangladesh. First the batsmen surrendered with a paltry score of 106. The bowlers tried their best under lights and though there was not a lot of movement or help from the surface, they managed to pick up 3 wickets. Ebadot was expensive but got 2 wickets. Al-Amin was the other bowler to get into the wickets column. It will be another long day for the visitors if they don't manage to keep picking up wickets.

A historic day has come to an end and it was another dominant day of play for India. They initially bowled out Bangladesh for just 106 and then they have managed to finish the evening's play with a lead of 68. The hosts lost the openers relatively early but the duo of Pujara and Kohli added 94 runs. Both got to their respective half tons but Pujara once again failed to convert his start. The Indian skipper and his deputy have added unbeaten 37 runs and would look to add more on Day 2.
